CORRUPTION and fraud accused Maphoko Hudson Kgomoeswana appeared in the Pretoria Regional Court on additional charges of tax evasion valued at R5 million on Thursday. The court postponed the matter to 15 April for the setting of a provisional date. According to Investigative Directorate spokeswoman Sindisiwe Twala, the tax fraud charges were discovered during the investigation of the controversial R745 million Eskom Kusile Power Station corruption case. She said the Limpopo businessman and his company are accused of facilitating bribes in the fraud and corruption matter, and he is currently out on R300 000 bail. “In the tax matter, he is charged with his company, Babinatlou Business Services CC, with evading income tax and company tax between the period 2016-2018,” she said.